pageContext.claim: “And you know in Portland, you see what happened last night? They arrested over 50 people the first time. We said, either do it or we're going in. We're going to have to go in.”
pageContext.analysis: This is puzzling. Federal agents had been in Portland for more than a month when the president said he threatened “either do it or we’re going in.” Moreover, the scale of the protests and the violence at the protests has expanded dramatically in response to the arrival of federal forces.
